verses.text: A prayer of Habakkuk the prophet upon Shigionoth.\f + \fr 3.1 \ft upon…: or, according to variable songs, or, tunes, called in Hebrew, Shigionoth\f*

O 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, I have heard thy speech , \add and\add* was afraid : O 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, revive thy work in the midst of the years , in the midst of the years make known ; in wrath remember mercy.  +  r 3.2  t speech: Heb. report, or, hearing *  +  r 3.2  t revive: or, preserve alive * \p
God came from Teman , and the Holy One from mount Paran. Selah. His glory covered the heavens , and the earth was full of his praise.\f + \fr 3.3 \ft Teman: or, the south\f*

And \add his\add* brightness was as the light ; he had horns \add coming\add* out of his hand : and there \add was\add* the hiding of his power.\f + \fr 3.4 \ft horns…: or, bright beams out of his side\f*
Before him went the pestilence , and burning coals went forth at his feet.\f + \fr 3.5 \ft coals: or, diseases\f*
He stood , and measured the earth : he beheld , and drove asunder the nations ; and the everlasting mountains were scattered , the perpetual hills did bow : his ways \add are\add* everlasting.

I saw the tents of Cushan in affliction : \add and\add* the curtains of the land of Midian did tremble.\f + \fr 3.7 \ft Cushan: or, Ethiopia\f*\f + \fr 3.7 \ft in…: or, under affliction, or, vanity\f*

Was the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* displeased against the rivers ? \add was\add* thine anger against the rivers ? \add was\add* thy wrath against the sea , that thou didst ride upon thine horses \add and\add* thy chariots of salvation ?\f + \fr 3.8 \ft of…: or, were salvation?\f*

Thy bow was made quite naked , \add according\add* to the oaths of the tribes , \add even thy\add* word. Selah. Thou didst cleave the earth with rivers.\f + \fr 3.9 \ft earth…: or, rivers of the earth\f*
The mountains saw thee, \add and\add* they trembled : the overflowing of the water passed by : the deep uttered his voice , \add and\add* lifted up his hands on high.

The sun \add and\add* moon stood still in their habitation : at the light of thine arrows they went , \add and\add* at the shining of thy glittering spear.\f + \fr 3.11 \ft at the light…: or, thine arrows walked in the light\f*
Thou didst march through the land in indignation , thou didst thresh the heathen in anger.

Thou wentest forth for the salvation of thy people , \add even\add* for salvation with thine anointed ; thou woundedst the head out of the house of the wicked , by discovering the foundation unto the neck. Selah.\f + \fr 3.13 \ft by…: Heb. making naked\f*

Thou didst strike through with his staves the head of his villages : they came out as a whirlwind to scatter me: their rejoicing \add was\add* as to devour the poor secretly.\f + \fr 3.14 \ft came…: Heb. were tempestuous\f*
Thou didst walk through the sea with thine horses , \add through\add* the heap of great waters.\f + \fr 3.15 \ft heap: or, mud\f* \p

When I heard , my belly trembled ; my lips quivered at the voice : rottenness entered into my bones , and I trembled in myself, that I might rest in the day of trouble : when he cometh up unto the people , he will invade them with his troops.\f + \fr 3.16 \ft invade…: or, cut them in pieces\f* \p

¶ Although the fig tree shall not blossom , neither \add shall\add* fruit \add be\add* in the vines ; the labour of the olive shall fail , and the fields shall yield no meat ; the flock shall be cut off from the fold , and \add there shall be\add* no herd in the stalls :\f + \fr 3.17 \ft fail: Heb. lie\f*
Yet I will rejoice in the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, I will joy in the God of my salvation.

The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd* God \add is\add* my strength , and he will make my feet like hinds’ \add feet\add*, and he will make me to walk upon mine high places. To the chief singer on my stringed instruments.\f + \fr 3.19 \ft chief…: or, overseer\f*\f + \fr 3.19 \ft stringed…: Heb. Neginoth\f*
